list.abstract: adequate，英 [ˈædɪkwət]，美 [ˈædɪkwət]。英语单词，形容词，指的是足够的；能满足需要的。短语搭配为“adequate resources（充足资源；适当资源；足够资源）” 例句为：“They depend on adequate sleep to thrive.（他们依靠充足的睡眠来茁壮成长。）” adequate近义词为suitable，competent。反义词为inadequate。

yingyinNormal.en: When Sheldon showers second, any and all measures shall be taken to ensure an adequate supply of hot water.
yingyinNormal.zh: "当谢尔顿第二个洗澡时必须采取各种方法保证有足够的热水"。

yingyinNormal.en: I find it perfectly adequate. Even if society is a little less varied than in town.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我觉得非常的适当，乡下碰不到像城里那么多些各色各样的人。

yingyinNormal.en: Bender and Sol here correctly completed Allen's proof of Peyrot's Conjecture. Adequate work without innovation.
yingyinNormal.zh: 本德和索尔已经成功的完成了柏瑞特推论的艾伦证明法。做的不错就是缺少创新。

yingyinNormal.en: What can be more special than having an adequate amount of time to cross the street on your way to buy a tiny LEGO Indiana Jones?
yingyinNormal.zh: 有什么能比在去买乐高夺宝奇兵模型的路上能有充足时间过马路更特别啊？
